description._content: Catalog #: 09_01570 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Unidentified man in beaver fur hat with martin B-10 aircraft in background, Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Corporation Name: Glenn L. Martin Company Tags: Elwyn H.
